Deputy President William Ruto on Saturday congratulated his wife Rachel who graduated on Friday, calling her "God's best gift"."My dear wife and best friend congratulations on your graduation with MA .You are God's best gift to me and the kids," Ruto said on Twitter.Rachel, who graduated with a Masters degree from one of the local universities, has been vocal on education initiatives in Kenya.She also runs the Joyful Women Organisation, which helps women get involved in table banking.Rachel has largely been absent since the launch of the Jubilee Party at Kasarani Stadium in September.She and the DP got married in 1991 and have six children.